OAuth / Subscription Credential Files
======================================

These files are bind-mounted directly into worker containers so that
all workers share the same credentials. You only need to log in once
after installing Agentor — the credentials are written back to these
files automatically and propagate to all workers instantly.

IMPORTANT: Do NOT copy OAuth tokens from your local machine. OAuth
refresh tokens rotate on use, so copying them would cause the local
and worker tokens to go out of sync and break authentication on both
sides. Always log in inside a worker instead.

API keys (always-valid, no rotation) remain in .env.

Setup:
  cp -r .cred.example .cred

Then start a worker and log in to each agent you want to use:

claude.json
-----------
Path in worker: ~/.claude/.credentials.json
Log in once: open a worker terminal, run `claude`, then use `/login`.
The credentials are written back to this file automatically and all
current and future workers are authenticated.

codex.json
----------
Path in worker: ~/.codex/auth.json
Log in once: open a worker terminal, run `codex login --device-auth`.
The credentials are written back to this file automatically and all
current and future workers are authenticated.

gemini.json
-----------
Path in worker: ~/.gemini/oauth_creds.json
Log in once: open a worker terminal, run `gemini`, then use `/auth`.
The credentials are written back to this file automatically and all
current and future workers are authenticated.
